    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is too spooky, surprising, and unconstrained in its scope. It affects all our tests, not just the ones that are currently flaking. Any integration or system tests that use the go test framework will get different behavior than they would in production, withoutout any explicit configuration.\n\nIf you need to adjust these timeouts, pipe them thru the front door like all the other options we have.",
